solution: ```class MKAverage {
    private final int m, k;
    private final Deque<Integer> dq;
    private final int[] freq, sorted;

    public MKAverage(int m, int k) {
        this.m = m;
        this.k = k;
        this.dq = new ArrayDeque<>();
        this.freq = new int[100_001];
        this.sorted = new int[m];
    }

    public void addElement(int num) {
        dq.addLast(num);
        freq[num]++;
        if (dq.size() > m) {
            int removed = dq.removeFirst();
            freq[removed]--;
        }
    }

    public int calculateMKAverage() {
        if (dq.size() < m) return -1;
        int idx = 0;
        for (int v = 1; v <= 100_000; v++) {
            int cnt = freq[v];
            while (cnt-- > 0) sorted[idx++] = v;
        }
        long sum = 0;
        for (int i = k; i < m - k; i++) sum += sorted[i];
        return (int) (sum / (m - 2 * k));
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(m log m) per calculateMKAverage, O(1) per addElement
space complexity: O(m)
